President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring September 9-11, 2016 as National Days of Prayer and Remembrance. The proclamation pays tribute to the lives lost on September 11, 2001 and encourages Americans to honor and remember the victims through various activities such as prayer, memorial services, visiting memorials, and candlelight vigils. The proclamation also emphasizes the heroism, compassion, and unity of the American people in the face of terrorism and hatred. President Obama invites people around the world to participate in commemorating this solemn anniversary.